{
  "stem": "12447.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was kind of-- because of my birthday, I wasn't even six years old when they put me to school because the school year started in September.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went into school, and I remember my first day I met the teacher and some children by registration.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the following day, I had to go to school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was scared, and I didn't really want to go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I carried on the whole morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I used to tell them, well, maybe I will go, maybe I wouldn't go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that went through the whole morning until I finally got enough guts, I suppose, to give my hand to my mother.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she walked me because I was afraid to walk by myself to school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was quite a distance from our house to school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was-- the, the school was on Zabkowska in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a Jewish-- what they call it a folkshul, a public Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was one of the few schools sponsored, I believe, by the Bund organization, the workers-- the Jewish workers of Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was sponsored by them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a Jewish school in the Polish language.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they also taught Jewish in school, as I can remember.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was probably supported by the Polish government-- that's why maybe they gave it the Polish language as a main language.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember my first day when I finally got myself into the class.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, I got to like it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I didn't cause any problems anymore to my-- to my parents.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was a good boy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went to school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wasn't a very good pupil.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember that there were certain subjects that I couldn't comprehend.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
